3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with the efficiency of large networks, which could fall under the category of distributed computing. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with network performance, which could be relevant to social and information networks. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - While not directly related to the content of the paper, the use of MILP and heuristics could suggest a computational complexity aspect to the work.
